facilitate all needs:

105
00:08:08,149 --> 00:08:10,629
Health,
safety,

106
00:08:10,629 --> 00:08:15,919
control over one’s own life,
a social and a natural,

107
00:08:15,919 --> 00:08:19,029
or green,
environment!

108
00:08:19,029 --> 00:08:24,529
Of course the relations between these primary
needs can be complicated.

109
00:08:24,529 --> 00:08:30,740
For example higher densities,
which often lead to opportunities for inhabitants,

110
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:33,899
might come with air pollution,
noise,

111
00:08:33,899 --> 00:08:37,449
less green ,and maybe unsafely.

112
00:08:37,449 --> 00:08:41,329
Now please question yourself,
how can these primary needs,

113
00:08:41,329 --> 00:08:48,220
illustrated on neighborhood level,
also contribute to socially sustainable mega-cities?

114
00:08:48,220 --> 00:08:55,769
It is all about balancing and finding advanced
metropolitan solutions!

